content.description: Yet another crazy, powerful endurance route that might not contain a lot of vertical feet, but somehow, every move is a crux. Expect no mercy.
content.location: Left most route. If you go any farther left you will end up at The Delicacy Wall.

content.description: A super-sick, blonde beauty -with exceptional moves- that require what just might be the sharpest crimp on Earth.

A short power endurance route with deliciously long moves. Might not be as hard as The Dank's Booze Cruise but this is definitely a route that will have you fighting all the way to the end. 

  Expect to be forced to do a whole lot with very few holds that are thin as sin. This route has great movement that flows well once you know the sequence. You get one big hold to rest on before the crux at the top gets real. Don't bother looking for a jug to clip the anchors from. It's just ain't there. An awesome route for those who love powerful, precise movement on crispy crimps. GET ON IT!
content.protection: 5 bolts. Open anchors. The first bolt is very high off the ground.

content.description: A killer wall with three really sweet power endurance routes that look small but climb big. Located between The Delicacy Wall and The Dojo. Recommended for those who love short, powerful routes with secret sequences. Not recommended for those whose skin has been thrashed after a week of crimping. This wall is full of sharp, tiny holds that require some fresh flesh.
